Text.Value: Tsk'va! The zaith'isk - it might have killed you. I felt your torment.
Few would dare dishonour their queen. Fewer still would be so brazen.
There was nothing to be done. The ghustil corrupted the machine - it must be so.
I followed protocol. I kept to my faith. Yet the zaith'isk might have killed me.

EditorData.logicalname: Not yet betrayed, dr. still in room

Text.Value: Someone must have tampered with it. An aberrance I can't begin to comprehend.
The ghustil tampered with it. Traitor - and there may be more still! This must be why the Inquisitor's come.
Then we agree. Go - quickly.
Vlaakith must have some purpose, some design I'm not meant to see.
A traitorous doctor? How can you be so sure?
How about a 'thank you'? I just saved your life.
We must inform the Inquisitor. The crèche is in danger.
Vlaakith's does not abandon githyanki. The zaith'isk was tampered with. There is no other explanation.

EditorData.logicalname: Not been betrayed by Vlaakith yet

Text.Value: The doctor, the Inquisitor - such heresy beggars belief. To the command centre. We might find a way to inform Vlaakith of their treason.

EditorData.logicalname: Started conflict with Inquisitor, but not betrayed by Vlaakith yet

Text.Value: Now hurry. We must go to the ch'r'ai and inform him of the zaith'isk's tampering.

EditorData.logicalname: Not started conflict with Inquisitor - dr still present

Text.Value: There must be Hshar'lak in this crèche - a traitor. The sort that is hunted, slaughtered, and erased from our histories.
A deception - proof of the doctor's manipulations. The queen does not mislead Gith's children.

EditorData.logicalname: Not been betrayed by Vlaakith yet

Text.Value: The zaith'isk, the Inquisitor - such aberrations beggar belief. To the command centre. We might find a way to inform Vlaakith of their treason.

EditorData.logicalname: Started conflict with Inquisitor, but not betrayed by Vlaakith yet

Text.Value: Now hurry. We must go to the ch'r'ai and inform him of the doctor's sedition.
In my queen, I trust. One day soon she will honour me for it. She must.
Are traitors so common among the githyanki?
'Thank you.' Happy? Good.
Vlaakith has taught us of Hshar'lak - traitors hunted, slaughtered, and erased from our histories.
You were so close to a cure, if only you'd held on longer...
The ghustil' must have tampered with it. An aberrance I can't begin to comprehend. As is all of Crèche Y'llek.
This zaith'isk is a deviation. It was altered - there is no other explanation.
I was so close to a cure. If only I'd held on longer...
The zaith'isk is supposed to kill you. I saw it for myself.
Who could have tampered with the device?
You have my thanks. Begrudgingly.

Synopsis: Laezel reacts on the Zaithisk being a lie. Should point to the Inqusitor if the conflict with him hasn't started, or at the inquisitor's office if it has. If Vlaakith betrayal has already happened, should point that she needs time to reflect on this.
